Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.

Thinly slice @zucchini{1} into rounds. Cut @red onion{1} into thick wedges.

Roughly chop @mild chorizo{250%g}.

Place zucchini, mild chorizo and onion on a lined #oven tray{}. Drizzle with
@olive oil{1%drizzle}, season with @salt{} and toss to coat.

Roast until lightly browned and cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, thinly slice @heirloom tomato{2} into rounds lengthways.

Finely chop @garlic{2}.

Roughly chop @capers{1%packet}.

Pick @thyme{1%sachet} leaves.

In a medium #heatproof bowl{}, place garlic and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle}.

Microwave until fragrant, ~{10%second} bursts.

Add @cream cheese{1%packet}, the @salt{} and a pinch of @pepper{}. Mix until well
combined.

Once veggies and chorizo are done roasting, evenly stack 5 sheets of
@filo pastry{1%packet} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} between each layer
and place on a second lined #oven tray{}.

Spread cream cheese mixture over the centre of the pastry, leaving a 4cm boarder
around the edges.

Top evenly with roasted veggies and chorizo and heirloom tomato slices.

Sprinkle with thyme leaves, drizzle with @olive oil{1%drizzle} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Carefully fold pastry edges over filling, leaving the centre exposed.

Bake tarts until golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Sprinkle tart with capers and dollop with @basil pesto{1%packet}.

Slice tart.

Divide roasted heirloom chorizo, tomato and cream cheese tart between plates.

Serve with @rocket{1%packet}. Enjoy!